# Description:
This program prompts the user for pairwise data, using *scanf()*,
which represents data collected during a ghost hunt.
This data is then printed in a nice way using *printf()*.
The data is also ordered using a sorting algorithm.

# Compilation and Execution
Assuming the files *main.c* and *readings.c* are in your current directory,
entering  *gcc -Wall main.c readings.c -o a1* into the command line will create an executable file called *a1*.
Entering *./a1* into the command line will run the program.